					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Thanks for the responses guys. I'll study what you were saying blargg. I am actually going to create a nice macro for this (I've created macros for lots of other branch conditions with WLA-DX), so I don't have to think about typing it in. It's obviously more intuitive to write something like:
<br />
<br />checkAgreaterthanBsigned(A,B,Label)
<br />
<br />Where it branches to "Label" if A is greater than B. Though I have a system where I shorten the words to:
<br />
<br />csAgtB
<br />
<br />Which stands for: check (signed) if A is greater than B. I have these handy macros for 16 bit comparisons where I can just quickly type that in without thinking (and sometimes, I get confused with comparisons, so I'll sit there and waste coding time thinking about how to compare two numbers).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

